THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

25:31.664 --> 25:33.904
FEEDING THE POOR
IS THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

25:33.933 --> 25:35.703
HIRING THE HANDICAPPED
IS THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

25:35.735 --> 25:37.165
DONATING BLOOD IS THE RIGHT--
- ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

25:37.203 --> 25:38.713
YOU MADE YOUR POINT.

25:38.738 --> 25:40.668
- EVERYONE LOVES
YOUR DRAWINGS.

25:40.707 --> 25:42.637
- YOU GUYS CHECK OUT THE FOOD?
- I'M NOT HUNGRY.

25:42.675 --> 25:43.735
- OKAY.
HOW ABOUT THE CUTE GUYS?

25:43.776 --> 25:47.146
THERE'S SOME RIGHT OVER THERE
JUST ABOUT YOUR AGE.

25:51.918 --> 25:53.888
- HE'S HERE.

25:53.920 --> 25:56.620
- HMM. YIPPEE.

25:56.656 --> 25:59.756
- WELL, AREN'T YOU GOING
TO GO OVER THERE?

25:59.792 --> 26:02.132
- ARE YOU CRAZY?

26:02.161 --> 26:05.131
- THANKS FOR COMING.

26:05.164 --> 26:07.604
- WHATEVER.

26:10.336 --> 26:11.866
WHERE'S THE BACK ROOM?

26:15.708 --> 26:18.078
- LINDSAY, THIS IS DAVID.

26:18.110 --> 26:20.280
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

26:20.312 --> 26:22.682
- WHOO! MICHAEL.

26:22.715 --> 26:23.715
- [clears throat]

26:23.750 --> 26:25.890
LET'S GO CHECK OUT
THE VAGINA SCULPTURES FIRST,

26:25.918 --> 26:28.118
GET IT OVER WITH.

26:32.992 --> 26:35.762
- THE FAMOUS ARTISTE.

26:35.795 --> 26:36.955
- OH, DID YOU SEE MY STUFF?

26:36.996 --> 26:38.256
- NO, I HAD TO GET
A DRINK FIRST.

26:38.297 --> 26:40.967
- IT'S OVER THERE...

26:41.000 --> 26:43.670
IN CASE YOU'RE INTERESTED.

27:00.352 --> 27:02.252
- PSST.

27:03.990 --> 27:07.390
- I THINK THE ARTIST
HAS TAKEN SOME LIBERTIES.

27:07.426 --> 27:09.396
- OH, THAT'S
A PERFECT LIKENESS.

27:09.428 --> 27:12.668
- COME ON,
IT WAS NEVER THAT BIG.

27:12.699 --> 27:15.329
- HEY, YOU HAVEN'T SEEN IT
IN A LONG TIME.

27:15.367 --> 27:16.397
- I HAVEN'T SEEN
GONE WITH THE WIND

27:16.435 --> 27:17.735
IN A LONG TIME EITHER,

27:17.770 --> 27:20.210
BUT I KNOW
IT'S STILL 3 1/2 HOURS.

27:20.239 --> 27:22.069
- THE BRIAN AND MICHAEL SHOW--

27:22.108 --> 27:23.978
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

27:24.010 --> 27:28.080
STUCK IN PERPETUAL RERUNS.

27:28.114 --> 27:31.824
- IS IT ALWAYS LIKE THAT--
MICHAEL RUNNING AFTER HIM?

27:31.851 --> 27:34.921
- IT'S THE GREATEST LOVE STORY
NEVER TOLD, TRUST ME.

27:34.954 --> 27:36.764
WHAT WAS YOUR NAME?

27:36.789 --> 27:37.759
- DAVID.

27:37.790 --> 27:38.760
- MELANIE.

27:38.791 --> 27:40.091
TRUST ME, DAVID,

27:40.126 --> 27:41.856
LONG AFTER YOU'RE GONE,
HE'LL STILL HAVE MICHAEL--

27:41.894 --> 27:44.134
BRIAN'S LITTLE ACOLYTE,
POOR GUY.

27:44.163 --> 27:45.803
OH, BUT DON'T WORRY.
MICHAEL CAN WAIT FOREVER.

27:45.832 --> 27:47.972
BRIAN'LL NEVER FUCK HIM.
PARDON MY FRENCH.

27:48.000 --> 27:50.200
- BY THE WAY, I HEARD YOU
HIT ON DAVID LAST NIGHT.

27:50.236 --> 27:51.296
- [scoffs]

27:51.337 --> 27:52.907
I COULDN'T HAVE BEEN
THAT HIGH.

27:52.939 --> 27:55.879
- YOU WERE.
AND YOU DID.

27:55.908 --> 27:57.008
- I WAS TESTING HIM.

27:57.043 --> 27:59.313
I WANTED TO SEE IF HE'D DROP YOU
THE FIRST CHANCE HE GOT.

27:59.345 --> 28:02.205
- OH, YEAH, RIGHT.

28:02.248 --> 28:04.978
- AREN'T I ALWAYS LOOKING OUT
FOR YOU?

28:05.017 --> 28:07.287
- YOU'RE JUST JEALOUS
BECAUSE SOMEBODY FINALLY THINKS

28:07.319 --> 28:10.859
I'M HOT OR SOMETHING.

28:10.890 --> 28:12.790
- YOU ARE HOT OR SOMETHING.

28:12.825 --> 28:14.985
I'VE BEEN TELLING YOU THAT
SINCE YOU WERE 14.

28:15.027 --> 28:17.827
BUT YOU WON'T BELIEVE ME.

28:21.267 --> 28:24.967
- SO I SUPPOSE I JUST KEEP HIM
COMPANY WHILE MICHAEL WAITS.

28:25.004 --> 28:25.974
- OH--

28:26.005 --> 28:27.835
OH, SHIT!

28:27.874 --> 28:31.184
OH, YOU'RE WITH MICHAEL.
- YEAH.

28:31.210 --> 28:33.050
- UM, OH, JESUS,

28:33.079 --> 28:34.309
I, UM--
I'M--I'M SORRY.

28:34.346 --> 28:35.916
I-I DIDN'T MEAN THAT.
I-I MEAN--

28:35.948 --> 28:37.918
WELL, I MEAN,
BRIAN'S THE ONE

28:37.950 --> 28:39.450
THAT'S ALWAYS SHOWING UP
WITH SOME NEW GUY,

28:39.485 --> 28:41.345
SO I JUST ASSUMED
THAT, UM...

28:41.387 --> 28:43.087
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

28:43.122 --> 28:44.792
- WELL, YOU KNOW THAT--

28:44.824 --> 28:46.934
THEY LOVE EACH OTHER AS FRIENDS,
BUT THAT'S IT.

28:46.959 --> 28:48.389
THAT'S REALLY--
THAT'S ALL IT IS.

28:48.427 --> 28:49.497
- REALLY?

28:49.528 --> 28:51.858
IT'S NOT LIKE I DIDN'T KNOW.

28:51.898 --> 28:54.428
- DO YOU WANT A SHRIMP BALL?

28:54.466 --> 28:56.496
- NO.

28:56.535 --> 28:58.435
THANKS.

29:03.442 --> 29:04.912
- [mouths word]

29:12.418 --> 29:16.858
- NOW, THAT'S
WHAT I CALL A PIECE...

29:16.889 --> 29:17.989
OF ART.

29:18.024 --> 29:19.394
- [snickers]

29:19.425 --> 29:21.525
I'VE ALWAYS ADMIRED
CREATIVE PEOPLE.

29:21.560 --> 29:25.000
- YOU'RE PRETTY CREATIVE
YOURSELF THERE, MISSY.

29:25.031 --> 29:28.271
- [scoffs]
NOT ME.

29:28.300 --> 29:31.300
BUT MICHAEL--
HE'S GOT A GIFT.

29:31.337 --> 29:33.067
- I DIDN'T KNOW
HE COULD DRAW.

29:33.105 --> 29:34.835
- OH, HE CAN'T.

29:34.874 --> 29:36.984
I BOUGHT HIM TRACING PAPER
WHEN HE WAS A KID

29:37.009 --> 29:38.409
SO HE COULD COPY
HIS COMIC BOOKS.

29:38.444 --> 29:40.884
HIS SPIDER-MAN ALWAYS ENDED UP

29:40.913 --> 29:43.053
LOOKING MORE LIKE
LITTLE ORPHAN ANNIE.

29:43.082 --> 29:45.482
- WELL, WHAT'S HIS TALENT?

29:45.517 --> 29:48.887
- WELL, IT'S NOTHING
HE'D BE FAMOUS FOR.

29:48.921 --> 29:51.421
YOU WON'T EVER SEE
HIS PAINTINGS

29:51.457 --> 29:52.857
HANGING IN AN ART GALLERY

29:52.892 --> 29:57.432
OR HEAR HIM PLAYING
AT CARNEGIE HALL.

29:57.463 --> 30:00.373
BUT WHEN IT COMES
TO TAKING CARE OF PEOPLE,

30:00.399 --> 30:04.299
KNOWING WHAT YOU NEED
BETTER EVEN THAN YOU DO,

30:04.336 --> 30:07.336
HE'S A FUCKING PICASSO.

30:40.206 --> 30:41.936
- BEAUTIFUL LIGHT AND SHADOW.

30:41.974 --> 30:43.884
- VERY...

30:43.910 --> 30:46.110
HAUNTING.

30:46.145 --> 30:48.605
- THE PHOTOGRAPHER
HAS A GREAT EYE.

30:48.647 --> 30:50.417
- STRONG...

30:50.449 --> 30:52.549
COMPOSITION.

30:52.584 --> 30:54.224
- YOU CAN'T STAY.
YOU HAVE TO LEAVE.

30:54.253 --> 30:55.963
- NOW, JUSTIN,
DON'T BE MEAN.

30:55.988 --> 30:57.458
I'VE KEPT MY END
OF THE BARGAIN.

30:57.489 --> 31:00.489
NOW, I WOULD LIKE TO SEE
MY SON'S WORK.

31:00.526 --> 31:02.626
I WON'T EMBARRASS YOU,
I PROMISE.

31:02.661 --> 31:04.931
- JUSTIN, IS THIS YOUR MOTHER?

31:04.964 --> 31:06.404
- HI, I'M JENNIFER.

31:06.432 --> 31:08.232
- MELANIE.
- LINDSAY.

31:08.267 --> 31:11.067
YOU KNOW,
YOUR SON'S REMARKABLY TALENTED.

31:11.103 --> 31:12.443
YOU SHOULD BE VERY PROUD.

31:12.471 --> 31:15.541
- WELL, THANK YOU.
I AM.

31:15.574 --> 31:18.444
AND WHAT A BEAUTIFUL BABY.

31:18.477 --> 31:19.647
- HIS NAME'S GUS.

31:19.678 --> 31:21.348
- ACTUALLY, JUSTIN'S
THE ONE WHO NAMED HIM.

31:21.380 --> 31:22.920
- REALLY?

31:22.949 --> 31:24.379
WELL, THAT WAS
HIS TEDDY BEAR'S NAME.

31:24.416 --> 31:27.446
- AW!
- AW, A TEDDY BEAR.

31:27.486 --> 31:28.516
- MOM.

31:28.554 --> 31:31.124
- UM, ARE YOU THE MOTHER?

31:31.157 --> 31:34.487
- UH, YES, BUT WE'RE RAISING
HIM TOGETHER.

31:34.526 --> 31:36.396
- WELL, THAT'S WONDERFUL.

31:36.428 --> 31:38.928
I'VE NEVER MET
LESBIAN MOTHERS BEFORE.

31:38.965 --> 31:41.695
I MEAN, I-I READ
ABOUT YOU--THEM

31:41.733 --> 31:43.543
IN THE PAPERS ALL THE TIME.

31:43.569 --> 31:46.009
- SEEMS LIKE THERE'S
ALWAYS SOME JUDGE IN ALABAMA

31:46.038 --> 31:47.068
TRYING TO TAKE OUR KIDS AWAY.

31:47.106 --> 31:48.566
- THAT'S WHY I MARRIED
A LAWYER.

31:48.607 --> 31:51.407
[laughter]

31:52.711 --> 31:54.511
- HAVE YOU SEEN THE ART?

31:54.546 --> 31:55.976
- NOT YET.

31:56.015 --> 31:59.115
WHERE'S YOUR STUFF, HONEY?

32:02.688 --> 32:05.688
- SHE CAME.
THAT'S HUGE.

32:09.461 --> 32:11.161
- TREMENDOUS ENERGY.

32:11.197 --> 32:14.697
- IT REALLY COMES
RIGHT OUT AT YOU.

32:16.502 --> 32:19.042
ROGER...

32:19.071 --> 32:21.971
I THINK I'M READY.

32:22.008 --> 32:25.308
- I PROMISED TO PLAY
THE PIANO.

32:25.344 --> 32:26.514
- YOU'RE JUST VOLUNTEERING.

32:26.545 --> 32:29.445
- YOU'RE RIGHT.
FUCK 'EM!

33:11.357 --> 33:14.327
- WHO'S THAT GUY YOU DREW?

33:26.272 --> 33:29.242
[edgy music]

33:29.275 --> 33:37.245
*

34:04.576 --> 34:07.346
[opera music]

34:07.379 --> 34:08.409
[headboard knocks]

34:08.447 --> 34:10.417
- OH, SORRY!
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

34:10.449 --> 34:18.418
*

34:19.824 --> 34:22.784
[clock ticking]

34:22.828 --> 34:30.768
*

34:41.246 --> 34:43.777
[ticking intensifies]

34:47.485 --> 34:49.456
- OUCH!
- I'M SORRY.

34:49.487 --> 34:51.658
- IT'S OKAY.

34:51.690 --> 34:54.730
[clocks ticking louder]

34:54.760 --> 34:58.330
*

34:58.364 --> 35:00.234
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

35:00.266 --> 35:01.766
- WHAT?
- NO, I-I CAN'T.

35:01.800 --> 35:04.740
- WHAT IS IT?
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

35:04.770 --> 35:06.340
- IT JUST WON'T WORK.

35:06.372 --> 35:09.312
I THOUGHT I COULD DO THIS.
I REALLY DID.

35:09.341 --> 35:11.681
I MEAN, YOU ARE SO NICE

35:11.710 --> 35:14.650
AND SMART AND TALENTED.

35:14.680 --> 35:16.750
AND YOU PLAY THE PIANO
BEAUTIFULLY.

35:16.782 --> 35:18.782
- BUT?

35:18.817 --> 35:20.517
WELL...

35:20.552 --> 35:23.892
GO ON, SAY IT.

35:23.922 --> 35:25.662
- YOU'RE JUST NOT MY TYPE.

35:25.691 --> 35:29.361
- "TYPE"?

35:29.395 --> 35:32.495
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

35:32.531 --> 35:35.171
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.
AFTER ALL THAT?

35:35.201 --> 35:38.241
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T WANT SEX
TO BE EVERYTHING.

35:38.270 --> 35:40.170
- YEAH, BUT...

35:40.206 --> 35:43.576
I'D LIKE IT
TO BE SOMETHING.

35:46.712 --> 35:49.152
- YOU'RE JUST LIKE
ALL THE OTHERS.

35:53.652 --> 35:56.262
[muttering]
WHERE'S MY SOCK?

35:56.288 --> 35:59.328
- LOOK, IT'S MY FAULT.
I ADMIT IT.

35:59.358 --> 36:01.288
I MEAN, I-I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THE HELL'S WRONG WITH ME.

36:01.327 --> 36:03.357
I MEAN, YOU'RE A CATCH.

36:03.395 --> 36:06.695
ANY STRAIGHT WOMAN WOULD FIND
YOU INCREDIBLY ATTRACTIVE.

36:06.732 --> 36:08.832
- OH, IS THAT SUPPOSED
TO MAKE ME FEEL BETTER?

36:08.867 --> 36:10.397
FUCK YOU.

36:10.436 --> 36:13.666
- LOOK, I KNOW WE SHARE
ALL THE IMPORTANT THINGS--

36:13.705 --> 36:16.405
MUSIC, A SENSE OF HUMOR.

36:16.442 --> 36:18.942
THIS WOULD BE A TOTALLY
APPROPRIATE RELATIONSHIP FOR ME.

36:18.977 --> 36:22.277
THE ONLY PROBLEM IS
IS THAT SEX ISN'T APPROPRIATE.

36:22.314 --> 36:25.324
- YOU KNOW,
I WAS WRONG.

36:25.351 --> 36:28.521
YOU'RE NOT LIKE ALL THE OTHERS.
YOU'RE WORSE...

36:28.554 --> 36:30.564
BECAUSE YOU THINK KNOWING
SESTO'S ARIA

36:30.589 --> 36:32.959
FROM CLEMENZA DI TITO
SOMEHOW MAKES YOU BETTER.

36:32.991 --> 36:34.561
WELL, LET ME TELL YOU,

36:34.593 --> 36:36.433
YOU'RE NOTHING
BUT A PRETENTIOUS,

36:36.462 --> 36:38.462
SELF-INVOLVED, BORING ASSHOLE

36:38.497 --> 36:40.297
WHO'S STILL HANGING AROUND
WITH YOUNGER GUYS

36:40.332 --> 36:43.442
WHO DON'T WANT YOU
AND NEVER WILL.

36:43.469 --> 36:45.869
YOU'RE PATHETIC.

36:45.904 --> 36:48.014
- AND WHAT ABOUT YOU?

36:48.039 --> 36:51.579
YOU KNOW, AFTER YOU CONDUCT
YOUR 501ST TRIBUTE

36:51.610 --> 36:54.350
TO SONDHEIM,
YOU MIGHT TRY GOING TO A GYM.

36:54.380 --> 36:55.850
YOU KNOW,
GET ON A TREADMILL

36:55.881 --> 36:57.581
FOR ONCE IN YOUR LIFE,
WOULD YOU?

36:57.616 --> 37:01.886
AND DO SOMETHING
ABOUT YOUR BREATH!

37:01.920 --> 37:03.890
LISTEN...

37:08.460 --> 37:10.900
I DON'T SUPPOSE
WE COULD STILL BE FRIENDS.

37:17.303 --> 37:20.273
[opera music]

37:20.306 --> 37:28.246
*

37:30.549 --> 37:32.919
[dance music]

37:32.951 --> 37:35.491
- SO I THOUGHT,
OKAY, HE'S HAVING...

37:35.521 --> 37:37.421
EXPERIENCES.

37:37.456 --> 37:39.986
BUT WITH BOYS HIS OWN AGE.

37:40.025 --> 37:42.325
THIS MAN--

37:42.361 --> 37:43.661
HE MUST BE IN HIS 30s!

37:43.695 --> 37:45.395
- WELL, NOT YET,
BUT I'LL BE HAPPY

37:45.431 --> 37:46.771
TO TELL HIM YOU THOUGHT SO.

37:46.798 --> 37:48.598
- WELL, IT'S NOT RIGHT.

37:48.634 --> 37:49.904
- IT HAPPENS.

37:49.935 --> 37:53.035
- IF HIS FATHER FINDS OUT...
[scoffs]

37:54.706 --> 37:57.836
TELL ME ABOUT HIM--
THIS PERSON.

37:57.876 --> 37:58.876
I HAVE TO KNOW.

37:58.910 --> 38:02.880
- BRIAN KINNEY...

38:02.914 --> 38:05.754
GOD'S GIFT TO GAY P.A.

38:07.553 --> 38:09.523
THEY ALL WANT BRIAN.

38:09.555 --> 38:11.785
BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS
NO ONE CAN HAVE HIM.

38:11.823 --> 38:14.693
HE SCREWS THEM, BREAKS THEIR
HEART, AND THEY WISE UP--

38:14.726 --> 38:17.896
WELL, MOST OF THEM ANYWAY.

38:21.433 --> 38:24.603
- SO, THIS, UH...

38:24.636 --> 38:27.006
BRIAN KINNEY...

38:27.038 --> 38:29.638
HE'S GOING TO HURT MY SON.

38:29.675 --> 38:31.075
WHAT DO I DO?

38:31.109 --> 38:32.679
- NOTHING.

38:32.711 --> 38:35.681
THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN DO
WITHOUT MAKING IT WORSE.

38:35.714 --> 38:37.424
- HE'S ONLY 17.

38:37.449 --> 38:41.049
- HOW OLD WERE YOU
THE FIRST TIME?

38:41.086 --> 38:43.356
- 16.

38:43.389 --> 38:46.319
- 15.

38:49.528 --> 38:52.358
ANYWAY, IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL
ANY BETTER,

38:52.398 --> 38:54.698
I'VE KNOWN BRIAN
SINCE HE WAS 14.

38:54.733 --> 38:56.573
HE HASN'T CHANGED MUCH.

38:56.602 --> 38:59.712
IN FACT, I'D SAY HE AND JUSTIN
ARE PRETTY EVENLY MATCHED.

38:59.738 --> 39:02.508
- [sighs]

39:02.541 --> 39:04.711
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN BE SO ACCEPTING.

39:04.743 --> 39:06.113
- HONEY...

39:06.144 --> 39:08.854
JENNIFER...

39:08.880 --> 39:10.980
YOU DON'T HAVE
TOO MUCH CHOICE.

39:11.016 --> 39:13.716
ALL YOU CAN DO IS HOPE
THAT THEY'LL BE CAREFUL

39:13.752 --> 39:17.562
AND THAT THEY REMEMBER
YOUR PHONE NUMBER.

39:20.626 --> 39:22.156
- UGH.

39:22.193 --> 39:23.463
HERE.

39:23.495 --> 39:25.155
- DON'T YOU DARE.

39:25.196 --> 39:26.596
THIS IS ON ME.

39:26.632 --> 39:28.572
- THANKS.

39:28.600 --> 39:31.140
- OH, HERE...

39:31.169 --> 39:33.639
GIVE HIM WHAT HE NEEDS.

39:41.913 --> 39:45.023
[dance music]

39:45.050 --> 39:49.820
*

39:49.855 --> 39:53.725
- * HE'S A HUNK OF LOVE

39:53.759 --> 39:55.159
- ADMIT IT--

39:55.193 --> 39:57.163
YOU MISSED ALL THIS.

39:57.195 --> 39:59.055
- THE RAMPANT NARCISSISM,

39:59.097 --> 40:01.727
THE SLEAZE, THE DRUG USE?

40:01.767 --> 40:03.567
I DON'T THINK SO.

40:03.602 --> 40:05.502
- SO WHY'D YOU COME BACK?

40:05.537 --> 40:08.467
- WHEN I FIGURE IT OUT,
I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

40:08.507 --> 40:11.207
- OH, LOOK,
IT'S THE CAST OF ZOOM.

40:11.242 --> 40:12.712
- WE'RE CELEBRATING.

40:12.744 --> 40:14.454
JUSTIN SOLD SOME
OF HIS ART TODAY.

40:14.480 --> 40:16.450
- THE ONE OF YOU, NAKED.

40:16.482 --> 40:18.082
- WHO'D BUY THAT?

40:18.116 --> 40:21.116
- PROBABLY SOME DESPERATE QUEEN
WHO'S ALWAYS PINED FOR YOU.

40:21.152 --> 40:24.092
- OH, TED,
HOW THOUGHTFUL.

40:24.122 --> 40:25.892
[bottles clinking]

40:25.924 --> 40:31.864
- OH, MY GOD.
I USED TO LOVE THIS SONG.

40:31.897 --> 40:33.827
- * OOH, OOH

40:33.865 --> 40:35.625
- THEN LET'S DANCE.

40:35.667 --> 40:39.537
- * OOH, OOH

40:39.571 --> 40:43.611
- I GOT TO PEE.

40:43.642 --> 40:46.552
* OOH, OOH, OOH

40:46.578 --> 40:48.878
* YOU'RE THE STAR

40:48.914 --> 40:51.484
* IT'S WHO YOU ARE

40:51.517 --> 40:53.077
- OKAY, DR. FEELGOOD.

40:53.118 --> 40:55.618
LET ME SEE YOU SHAKE
YOUR GROOVE THANG.

40:55.654 --> 40:57.724
COME ON.

41:03.128 --> 41:04.828
OOH, HE CAN DANCE.

41:04.863 --> 41:06.703
HE'S GAY AFTER ALL.

41:06.732 --> 41:09.942
- * EVERYBODY KNOWS YOUR NAME

41:09.968 --> 41:13.198
* THEY WANT TO GET CLOSE
TO THAT FLAME *

41:13.238 --> 41:16.938
* YOU CAN SEE IT
ON EVERY FACE *

41:16.975 --> 41:19.605
- ANYBODY EVER TELL YOU
YOU'RE A BAD INFLUENCE?

41:19.645 --> 41:20.975
YOU ARE.

41:21.012 --> 41:25.722
- * THE DJ PLAYS
YOUR FAVORITE SONG *

41:25.751 --> 41:29.151
* EVERYONE WANTS TO SING ALONG

41:29.187 --> 41:32.657
* IT'S A FEELING
YOU CAN'T FIGHT *

41:32.691 --> 41:36.861
* 'CAUSE YOU'RE
THE STAR TONIGHT *

42:00.652 --> 42:02.152
- HI.

42:02.187 --> 42:04.117
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

42:04.155 --> 42:06.015
- BETTER...

42:06.057 --> 42:09.327
NO THANKS TO YOU.

42:09.360 --> 42:11.760
- I NEVER REALLY KNEW FOR SURE
WHAT HAPPENED THAT NIGHT.

42:11.797 --> 42:12.927
I FIGURED YOU CAME
OUT OF IT OKAY.

42:12.964 --> 42:14.634
I KEPT LOOKING IN THE PAPERS.

42:14.666 --> 42:17.696
- GEE, THAT'S
REALLY THOUGHTFUL.

42:17.736 --> 42:20.966
- I, UH...

42:21.006 --> 42:22.106
WAITED ON THE CORNER

42:22.140 --> 42:25.710
AFTER I CALLED THE PARAMEDICS,
TO MAKE SURE THEY CAME.

42:25.744 --> 42:29.754
- YOU MEAN YOU CALLED 911?

42:29.781 --> 42:32.051
- I DIDN'T WANT TO STICK AROUND.

42:32.083 --> 42:34.253
I WAS AFRAID--
YOU KNOW, THE DRUGS AND SHIT.

42:34.285 --> 42:35.745
- RIGHT.

42:35.787 --> 42:39.287
- I MEAN, YOU TOOK SO MUCH,
I WAS LIKE, "WHOA."

42:41.359 --> 42:45.029
ANYWAY,
I'M GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

42:46.732 --> 42:49.332
- WELL, UH...

42:49.367 --> 42:52.237
MAYBE WE COULD GET TOGETHER
AGAIN SOME TIME--

42:52.270 --> 42:53.940
I MEAN,
WITHOUT THE PARAMEDICS.

42:53.972 --> 42:56.112
- [chuckles]

42:56.141 --> 42:57.381
- THERE YOU ARE.

42:57.408 --> 42:59.238
WHAT'S TAKING YOU SO LONG?

42:59.277 --> 43:02.047
- JUST TALKING TO SOME GUY.

43:02.080 --> 43:05.280
WHAT'S YOUR NAME AGAIN?

43:05.316 --> 43:06.346
- TED.

43:06.384 --> 43:09.224
- TED, RIGHT.

43:09.254 --> 43:11.864
YEAH, I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

43:11.890 --> 43:15.960
- SEE YOU.

43:15.994 --> 43:23.804
*

43:25.203 --> 43:26.643
- HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?

43:26.672 --> 43:28.072
- NO!
- HI.

43:28.106 --> 43:30.376
HI, HOW ARE YOU?

43:30.408 --> 43:31.978
HI.

43:32.010 --> 43:33.950
HEY, HOW ARE...

43:33.979 --> 43:36.849
HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?

43:36.882 --> 43:37.922
IT'S A GREAT LITTLE...

43:37.949 --> 43:40.749
OW!

43:43.154 --> 43:44.724
- HOW'S IT GOING?

43:44.756 --> 43:47.286
YOU TWO ARE TOGETHER--
THAT'S TERRIFIC.

43:50.261 --> 43:53.731
- OH, MY GOD, YOU DID IT
IN THE LITTLE BOYS' ROOM.

43:53.765 --> 43:54.995
- NOPE.

43:55.033 --> 43:56.873
- YOU GOT SOMEBODY'S
PHONE NUMBER?

43:56.902 --> 44:00.912
- I WAS REJECTED BY EVERYBODY.

44:03.942 --> 44:05.882
IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK!

44:05.911 --> 44:07.881
[both laugh]

44:07.913 --> 44:09.683
- MWAH.

44:09.715 --> 44:10.775
- [laughs]

44:10.816 --> 44:13.916
- LET'S GET YOU A COCKTAIL.
- OKAY.

44:13.952 --> 44:18.292
*

